					h1 My life so far..
					h4 I was born in Las Cruces, New Mexico, briefly raised in Missouri, then spent the majority of my childhood in San Diego, California. I currently attend the University of California, Berkeley, where I am in my third year studying Computer Science, Cognitive Science. I’m actively involved in the UCJazz program, frequently gigging with my combos and trios (known as Saxadaisacal and CS^5), I’m an athlete on my university Triathlon team, a brother of Sigma Phi Epsilon Cal Alpha Chapter (or commonly known as Sigma “Tri” Epsilon), and dabble in as many random clubs as I can. 
					h4 I think a good general way to describe me is as an introspective introvert who loves to chase big dreams. 
					h4 I love getting tangled up in large-scale projects and get totally immersed in the state of flow, which is usually reached with the aid of some house, trance, EDM, or jazz music. I firmly agree with the latter side of the “Nature vs. Nurture” debate  (aside from physical limitations in athletics), and am a strong believer in a growth mindset. I currently strive to read as much as I can, and have recently committed myself to following my lost childhood passion to continue and pursue my musical aspirations. One day, I would love to be on the cognitive technology frontier and create an impact as a musician as well.
